DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260308T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260308T183000
DTSTAMP:20260308T170546
CREATED:20260227T184109Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260227T184109Z
UID:10075630-1772985600-1772994600@thedirt.online
SUMMARY:Becoming\, Belonging\, Being\, and Beyond
DESCRIPTION:A Filipino musical storytelling event \n  \nThis immersive experience weaves together storytelling and live Filipino music\, inviting the audience into a contemplative yet communal journey centered on the themes of Becoming\, Belonging\, Being\, and Beyond. \nThe narrative is anchored by the story of Dr. Julie Arellano\, alongside the inspiring stories of Filipino Americans in the Sacramento community—Claire Oliveros\, PhD\, Pauline Roselada\, Karlo Feliciano\, and Thea Feliciano. \nDr. Arellano is joined by Steven Johnson\, Eileen Lichnock\, and Dr. Alex Mallari in performing live Filipino music throughout the program. Their music lifts the stories and shapes the emotional arc of the evening. Earlier songs invite introspection and emotional depth\, gradually moving toward joyful celebration. The central role of music in the event mirrors its central role in Filipino culture. \nWhile rooted in Filipino culture\, the experience is designed to be meaningful for people of all backgrounds. It is intended to bring forth reflection on one’s own journey\, or that of one’s family—paths shaped by survival and the search for opportunity\, identity\, and home. \nLight audience participation opens the event\, followed by quiet listening during the narratives and music. Attendees engage in self-reflection with a workbook as their companion during this introspective phase. The event ends with a lively communal activity. Filipino food elements are included as part of the experience\, adding warmth and a sense of Filipino hospitality. \n  \nPresale through 3/7/26: $20 general admission; $15 for I-House members and students $25 at the door/$20 for students
URL:https://thedirt.online/event/becoming-belonging-being-and-beyond/
LOCATION:International House Davis\, 10 College Park\, Davis\, CA\, 95616\, United States
CATEGORIES:Bring the Kids,Community,Food & Drink,Music
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://thedirt.online/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/WT-2026-Becoming-Belonging-Being-and-Beyond-3.8.26-1.png
ORGANIZER;CN="International House Davis":MAILTO:shelly@ihousedavis.org
END:VEVENT
