SUMMARY:Davis Autonomy Expo
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T023000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260313T050000Z
UID:1dadd81d5b7d449cf4d3e5d092992b04292026_6:04:58_PM@campusgroups.com
DESCRIPTION:The Autonomous Robotics Showcase is an open-to-all-students de
 monstration event hosted by the Davis Autonomy Club. The event will featur
 e live robotics demonstrations including an Aloha Mini robotic arm perform
 ing autonomous manipulation tasks\, a leader-follower teleoperation statio
 n where attendees can physically control a robotic arm in real-time\, and 
 an AERO robotic hand demonstrating dexterous grasping and manipulation. Th
 e event will also include screen-based presentations of AI-controlled dron
 e flight and simulation environments\, brief keynote presentations on stud
 ent-led research in autonomous systems\, open networking time for students
  interested in robotics and AI\, and food and refreshments. Our goal is to
  make autonomous robotics accessible and exciting to the broader UC Davis 
 student body\, regardless of major or technical background. --- Event Deta
 ils: https://aggielife.ucdavis.edu/rsvp?id=908340
URL:https://aggielife.ucdavis.edu/rsvp?id=908340
X-SOURCE:UC Davis CampusGroups
END:VEVENT
